{
  "$comment": "THE single source of framework metadata for Flutter/Material (ADR-18). Generated into BOTH language domains — the analyzer's extraction adapter and the compiler's widget registry. Neither domain hand-writes any of this. A fact stated twice is a fact that will eventually be stated two different ways, and we have already paid for that twice: canonical numbers (100.0 vs 100) and this catalog (a flat slot set in Dart, a per-widget catalog in TypeScript).",

  "catalog": "material",
  "priority": 10,
  "library": "package:flutter/",

  "componentBases": [
    "StatelessWidget",
    "StatefulWidget",
    "InheritedWidget",
    "ConsumerWidget",
    "ConsumerStatefulWidget",
    "HookWidget",
    "HookConsumerWidget",
    "StatefulHookConsumerWidget"
  ],

  "stateBase": "State",

  "stateHolders": [
    "AnimationController",
    "ChangeNotifier",
    "ScrollController",
    "TextEditingController",
    "ValueNotifier"
  ],

  "storeBases": ["ChangeNotifier", "Notifier", "StateNotifier"],

  "lifecycle": {
    "initState": "mount",
    "didUpdateWidget": "update",
    "didChangeDependencies": "update",
    "dispose": "unmount"
  },

  "stateBatchCalls": ["setState"],

  "semantics": {
    "labelProps": ["semanticLabel"],
    "widgets": {
      "Semantics": { "label": "label", "hint": "hint", "excluded": "excludeSemantics" },
      "ExcludeSemantics": { "alwaysExcluded": true }
    }
  },

  "theme": {
    "types": ["ThemeData", "ColorScheme"],
    "seedConstructor": "fromSeed",
    "seedProp": "seedColor",
    "brightnessProp": "brightness",
    "nonRoleProps": ["brightness", "seedColor", "dynamicSchemeVariant"]
  },

  "widgets": [
    { "name": "Text", "role": "text" },
    { "name": "SelectableText", "role": "text" },

    { "name": "FutureBuilder", "role": "async" },
    { "name": "StreamBuilder", "role": "async" },

    { "name": "Column", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "Row", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "Stack", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "Wrap", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "Flex", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "ListView", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "GridView", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "ListBody", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "ButtonBar", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "OverflowBar", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "TabBarView", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "PageView", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "Table", "childrenProp": "children" },

    {
      "$comment": "The reason this migration exists. `slivers` is an ordered child list under a name that is not `children` — and extraction, which hardcoded the literal string `children`, buried it in props as an opaque expression. CustomScrollView is the backbone of every scrolling Flutter screen.",
      "name": "CustomScrollView",
      "childrenProp": "slivers"
    },
    { "name": "SliverList", "childrenProp": "children" },
    { "name": "MultiSliver", "childrenProp": "children" },

    {
      "$comment": "`actions` is an ordered child list. One buried in hello_bridge's own props.",
      "name": "AppBar",
      "slots": ["title", "leading", "flexibleSpace", "bottom"],
      "childrenProp": "actions"
    },
    {
      "name": "SliverAppBar",
      "slots": ["title", "leading", "flexibleSpace", "bottom"],
      "childrenProp": "actions"
    },

    {
      "name": "Scaffold",
      "slots": [
        "appBar",
        "body",
        "bottomNavigationBar",
        "bottomSheet",
        "drawer",
        "endDrawer",
        "floatingActionButton"
      ],
      "childrenProp": "persistentFooterButtons"
    },

    { "name": "ListTile", "slots": ["leading", "title", "subtitle", "trailing"] },
    { "name": "MaterialApp", "slots": ["home"] },
    { "name": "CupertinoApp", "slots": ["home"] },
    { "name": "WidgetsApp", "slots": ["home"] },
    { "name": "Card", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "Dismissible", "slots": ["child", "background", "secondaryBackground"] },
    {
      "$comment": "`.extended` is a factory on the SAME class, so `icon` and `label` are parameters of FloatingActionButton itself. Extraction keys on the type, not the constructor — so the entry carries the union. A separate `FloatingActionButton.extended` entry was inert, and N8's verification is what found it.",
      "name": "FloatingActionButton",
      "slots": ["child", "icon", "label"]
    },
    { "name": "ElevatedButton", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "TextButton", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "OutlinedButton", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "IconButton", "slots": ["icon"] },

    {
      "$comment": "Wrappers whose identity IS their behaviour: no `transparentWithoutProps`, so they are never flattened. A `Center` with no props still centres. Guessing that a prop-less widget must be a pass-through is how a compiler silently deletes a layout.",
      "name": "Center",
      "slots": ["child"]
    },
    { "name": "Align", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "Padding", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "Expanded", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "Flexible", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "Positioned", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "SafeArea", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "AspectRatio", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "FittedBox", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "ClipRRect", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "Opacity", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "Transform", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "GestureDetector", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "InkWell", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "Semantics", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "SingleChildScrollView", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "Form", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "PopScope", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "ListenableBuilder", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "ColoredBox", "slots": ["child"] },
    { "name": "MergeSemantics", "slots": ["child"] },

    {
      "$comment": "Wrappers that CAN be transparent — a pass-through carrying none of the props that make it significant.",
      "name": "Container",
      "slots": ["child"],
      "transparentWithoutProps": [
        "alignment",
        "clipBehavior",
        "color",
        "constraints",
        "decoration",
        "foregroundDecoration",
        "height",
        "margin",
        "padding",
        "transform",
        "transformAlignment",
        "width"
      ]
    },
    { "name": "SizedBox", "slots": ["child"], "transparentWithoutProps": ["width", "height"] },
    { "name": "DecoratedBox", "slots": ["child"], "transparentWithoutProps": ["decoration"] },
    {
      "$comment": "A rendering hint with no layout or semantic effect. Every target repaints on its own terms, so it never survives to one — transparent with no conditions at all.",
      "name": "RepaintBoundary",
      "slots": ["child"],
      "transparentWithoutProps": []
    }
  ]
}
